task_description: Facing the building to your North-West (approx. 333°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: Moving to the front-left position (move 2) will bring me closer to the target building, providing a clearer view of its full structure from ground to roof to improve the height estimate accuracy.
Moving front (move 1) will bring me closer to the target building, making it easier to observe its full structure once I align my view to the North-West direction.

Based on the visual observation of the target building, estimating its height by comparing to surrounding trees (approx. 10m tall) and counting visible floors plus the dome structure, I estimate the total height to be 20 meters.
